But probably the thought is rather that she would make haste and let her young beauty‚ the hated cause of her present condition, gain her a death before it too vanished. It may at least be of some use if it makes her a dainty morsel for a tiger. She loathes her beauty: it is not that she would spare it from withering‚ or herself from seeing it wither.
